List MySQL Data Types

MySQL Data Types

In MySQL, data types define the type of data a column can store (number, text, date, etc.).

They are mainly divided into 3 major categories:

Numeric Data Types

Used to store numbers.

Integer Types

TINYINT

SMALLINT

MEDIUMINT

INT / INTEGER

BIGINT

Decimal Types

DECIMAL(p,s) → Exact decimal values

NUMERIC(p,s)

Floating Point Types

FLOAT

DOUBLE

Boolean

BOOLEAN (stores TRUE/FALSE as 1/0)

String (Character) Data Types

Used to store text.

Fixed Length

CHAR(n)

Variable Length

VARCHAR(n)

Large Text

TEXT

TINYTEXT

MEDIUMTEXT

LONGTEXT

Binary Strings

BINARY(n)

VARBINARY(n)

BLOB

TINYBLOB

MEDIUMBLOB

LONGBLOB

Date and Time Data Types

Used to store date and time values.

DATE → YYYY-MM-DD

TIME → HH:MM:SS

DATETIME

TIMESTAMP

YEAR

Other Data Types

ENUM → List of allowed values

SET → Multiple values from a list

JSON → Store JSON data